.PP
\[en] title: TRACEE\-LIST\-DETECTORS section: 1 header: Tracee List
Detectors Command Manual date: 2026/05 \&...
.SS NAME
tracee \f[B]list detectors\f[R] \- List available detectors and shared
lists
.SS SYNOPSIS
tracee \f[B]list detectors\f[R] [paths\&...]
[\-\-json]
.SS DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]list detectors\f[R] command displays all available detectors
and shared lists from built\-in sources and YAML files.
.PP
Detectors analyze events and produce threat detections or derived
events.
.PP
Shared lists are reusable value sets (e.g., shell binaries, sensitive
paths) that YAML detectors can reference in CEL expressions.
.SS ARGUMENTS
.TP
\f[B][paths\&...]\f[R]
Directories or files to search for YAML detectors and lists.
If not specified, uses default paths (/etc/tracee/detectors).
.SS FLAGS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-json\f[R], \f[B]\-j\f[R]
Output in JSON format for scripting.
.SS OUTPUT
The command displays two sections:
.SS Detectors
.TP
\f[B]ID\f[R]
Unique detector identifier (e.g., TRC\-001, DRV\-001)
.TP
\f[B]Name\f[R]
Detector event name
.TP
\f[B]Severity\f[R]
Threat severity level (info, low, medium, high, critical)
.TP
\f[B]Required Events\f[R]
Events the detector needs to receive
.TP
\f[B]MITRE\f[R]
MITRE ATT&CK technique ID if applicable
.SS Shared Lists
.TP
\f[B]Name\f[R]
List variable name (uppercase snake_case, e.g., SHELL_BINARIES)
.TP
\f[B]Values\f[R]
Number of values in the list
.TP
\f[B]Source\f[R]
Directory the shared list was loaded from (YAML scope for that list).
.SS JSON OUTPUT
When using \f[CR]\-\-json\f[R], the output structure is:
.IP
.EX
{
  \[dq]detectors\[dq]: [
    {
      \[dq]id\[dq]: \[dq]yaml\-001\[dq],
      \[dq]name\[dq]: \[dq]suspicious_exec\[dq],
      \[dq]severity\[dq]: \[dq]HIGH\[dq],
      \[dq]required_events\[dq]: [\[dq]sched_process_exec\[dq]],
      \[dq]mitre_technique\[dq]: \[dq]T1059\[dq]
    }
  ],
  \[dq]lists\[dq]: [
    {\[dq]name\[dq]: \[dq]SHELL_BINARIES\[dq], \[dq]value_count\[dq]: 6, \[dq]source_dir\[dq]: \[dq]/etc/tracee/detectors\[dq]},
    {\[dq]name\[dq]: \[dq]SENSITIVE_PATHS\[dq], \[dq]value_count\[dq]: 12, \[dq]source_dir\[dq]: \[dq]/etc/tracee/detectors\[dq]}
  ]
}
.EE
.SS EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
List all detectors and lists from default paths:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List detectors and lists from a custom directory:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors ./my\-detectors
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List detectors and lists from multiple directories:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors ./dir1 ./dir2
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List detectors and lists in JSON format:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors \-\-json
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Filter critical detectors with jq:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors \-\-json | jq \[aq].detectors[] | select(.severity == \[dq]CRITICAL\[dq])\[aq]
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List shared list names with jq:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors \-\-json | jq \[aq].lists[].name\[aq]
.EE
